race.description: Ladbrokes Future Stars Series Heat 7 Maiden Plate
race.comment: GENERAL BLU (4) looks the one to beat. He debuted at Geelong over 1125m and ran an eye-catching second, drawing wide there and getting right back to last before rattling home to be beaten a nose. He gets the golden switch to barrier two here and will take a power of beating. SPARKLING LUCK (8) resumes. He showed good ability in his debut campaign and has trialled well leading in. He can roll forward here and measure up with natural improvement. BRADFORD (1) was just fair in a similar race here fresh but should be fitter and can improve. CLANSMAN (3) is a Flying Artie gelding on debut for the Moloney yard who has trialled well leading in and can figure. Wary of MAHERSHALA (6) on debut for strong connections.
